====Synonyms====
*[[를]] (follows vowels)
*[[을]] (eul, follows consonants)
*[[ㄹ]] (l, follows vowels, colloquial)

====Translations====
*Hebrew: [[את]]
*Japanese: [[を]] (o)
*Spanish: [[a]] (only used when the object is a person)